Name: Eiffel Tower
Description: Eiffel Tower is a wrought-iron lattice tower on the Champ de Mars in Paris, France. It is named after the engineer Gustave Eiffel, whose company designed and built the tower.

Name: Louvre
Description: Louvre  is the world's largest art museum and a historic monument in Paris, France, and is best known for being the home of the Mona Lisa.
